value.title: Joe Biden to nominate Antony Blinken as US secretary of state
value.excerpt: Veteran diplomat may be named as early as Tuesday, with Linda Thomas-Greenfield to be ambassador to UN

value.title: Rudy Giuliani: Sidney Powell not part of Trump’s legal team
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump’s campaign on Sunday distanced itself from Sidney Powell, saying that the lawyer who has been alleging voter fraud in the November election is “not a member of the Trump Legal Team.”

value.title: Trump campaign parts ways with Powell after vote-switching claim
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump's election campaign on Sunday distanced itself from Sidney Powell, a lawyer who claimed at a news conference last week that electronic voting systems had switched millions of ballots to President-elect Joe Biden.

value.title: Biden expected to make trip to Georgia to stump for Ossoff, Warnock
value.excerpt: The push to win both races could see the Democrats pull a divided Senate, which would force both parties to work on passing any legislation.

value.title: Larry Hogan to Trump: 'Stop golfing and concede' the election
value.excerpt: Maryland Gov. Larry Hogan tore into President Trump on Sunday, telling the current White House resident to get off the golf course and concede to losing the election.

value.title: Stephen Moore says that Trump will leave office 'triumphant,' comparing him to Winston Churchill
value.excerpt: "Sometimes I think he's like Winston Churchill," Moore said of President Trump who took offense to similar comparisons made in the past.

value.title: Chris Christie calls Trump's legal team a 'national embarrassment'
value.excerpt: A staunch ally of Donald Trump said Sunday it was time for the President to end his futile gambit to overturn the results of the election.

value.title: Dershowitz: Trump has 'constitutional paths' to pursue in court cases, will likely come up short
value.excerpt: Harvard Law Professor Emeritus Alan Dershowitz said Sunday that while President Trump has a number of legal theories he can pursue in his efforts to swing the 2020 election result in his favor, it does not appear likely that these efforts will be successful.

value.title: Trump rails against Paris climate accord in virtual G20 event
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump railed against the Paris climate accord and touted American oil and natural gas production during a virtual session focused on safeguarding the environment on the final day of the Group of 20 summit.

value.title: LIVE UPDATES: Trump criticizes Biden forming Cabinet amid election legal challenges
value.excerpt: Follow for the latest updates on the 2020 election and transition.

value.title: Trump campaign requests Georgia recount that's unlikely to change his loss in the state
value.excerpt: Georgia will conduct another recount of its presidential ballots following a Trump campaign request Saturday, but the recount is extremely unlikely to change his loss in the state.

value.title: Donald Trump appears to admit Covid is 'running wild' in the US
value.excerpt: Comments, in contrast to pre-election rhetoric, come as FDA approves emergency use authorisation for Regeneron antibody therapy

value.title: Wisconsin officials: Trump observers obstructing recount
value.excerpt: Election officials in Wisconsin said Saturday that Trump poll watchers were “obstructing” the recount and acting in “bad faith” as tabulations continue in Milwaukee and Dane counties.

value.title: Rep.-elect August Pfluger of Texas calls Biden oil plans 'extremely alarming'
value.excerpt: An Air Force veteran newly elected to represent an oil-rich Texas district said President-elect Joe Biden's proposals on taxes, and the oil and gas industry are "extremely alarming."

value.title: Trump calls into virtual G20 summit, talks COVID-19 with world leaders
value.excerpt: President Trump took part in the first of two virtual meetings with world leaders Saturday as part of a coronavirus-throttled G20 summit — in what could be the last international gathering of his presidency.

value.title: McEnany: Trump's path to victory is Supreme Court, exposing 'systemic' voter fraud
value.excerpt: The path to challenging "systemic voter fraud" during the 2020 presidential election is through the courts, Trump campaign adviser Kayleigh McEnany said Saturday.

value.title: Who needs Russia? Loudest attacks on US vote are from Trump
value.excerpt: In the weeks before the presidential election, federal authorities warned that foreign countries could spread false information about the results to discredit the legitimacy of the outcome

value.title: Less pomp and circumstance? Biden inauguration likely to be scaled-down affair in response to COVID
value.excerpt: Joe Biden's inauguration in January is expected to look a lot different than previous presidential inaugurals. The reason: COVID.

value.title: Georgia certifies election results, making Biden victory official
value.excerpt: Georgia certified the general election Friday, officially making President-elect Biden the victor. The Trump campaign has until Tuesday to request a recount.

value.title: Biden team slams Treasury decision to curtail Fed lending powers, calls move ‘deeply irresponsible’
value.excerpt: The Federal Reserve and Treasury Department had a rare public falling out over whether the central bank should retain emergency lending powers.

value.title: Some Catholics sounding alarm about Biden administration, conflicts with moral teachings
value.excerpt: Some Catholic groups and leaders are warning that President-elect Biden would, despite being a member of the faith, enact harmful policies and create confusion about church teachings.

value.title: Trump takes credit for Pfizer vaccine development, says Americans wouldn’t have one yet without his leadership
value.excerpt: Pfizer announced it applied for emergency authorization use for its vaccine candidate on Friday.

value.title: Joe Biden's Irish ancestral hometown, Ballina, revels in win as London grows uneasy over Brexit
value.excerpt: Ballina, once known as the salmon fishing capital of Ireland, now boasts its very own incoming American president.

value.title: Coronavirus live news: Donald Trump Jr tests positive as Mexico deaths pass 100,000
value.excerpt: Obrador rejects criticism as political attacks; Canada fears big rise in cases could overwhelm hospitals; Italy records 37,242 new cases

value.title: Pence pitches Georgia senators as last line of GOP defense
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence campaigned Friday in Georgia in support of the state’s two Republican senators and warning of a potential Democratic takeover of Washington in January
